## Architecture Rules
{{if .Features.Backend}}
- Backend follows modular architecture.
- Domain does not depend on infrastructure.
- HTTP handlers do not contain business rules.
- Repositories do not return HTTP models.
- Errors must be typed and logged.
- Every new feature must have tests.
{{end}}
{{if .Features.Frontend}}
- Components must be reusable and tested.
- State management must be explicit.
- No inline styles without justification.
{{end}}

## Testing Rules

- Business rules require unit tests.
- Database integration requires integration tests.
- Critical routes require API tests.
{{if eq .Quality.Tests.E2E "required"}}- Main flows require e2e tests.{{end}}

## Documentation Rules

- Architecture changes require ADR.
{{if .Stack.Backend.APIContract}}- Endpoint changes require OpenAPI updates.{{end}}
- Environment variable changes require .env.example update.
- Infrastructure changes require docs/engineering update.

## Model Routing

{{if .Agents.Enabled}}
